==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wittily
<hw>Wit"ti*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a witty manner; wisely;
ingeniously; artfully; with wit; with a delicate turn or phrase, or with
an ingenious association of ideas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who his own harm so <qex>wittily</qex> contrives.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wittiness</ent>⟦br⟧
